sequenceDiagram
    participant Browser as Browser (SPA)
    participant IdP as IdP (Entra ID)
    participant Cognito as AWS Cognito
    participant DefineAuth as DefineAuthChallenge Lambda
    participant CreateAuth as CreateAuthChallenge Lambda
    participant VerifyAuth as VerifyAuthChallenge Lambda
    participant EnsureUser as EnsureCognitoUser Lambda
    participant PreToken as PreTokenGeneration Lambda
    participant Django as Django Backend

    Note over Browser,Django: Migration - first OIDC login. User not yet in Cognito.<br/>Frontend uses msal-angular which manages PKCE and Entra token exchange internally.<br/>No Hosted UI redirect - Cognito CUSTOM_AUTH used directly.

    Note over Browser: msal-angular authenticates with Entra ID.<br/>Returns Entra id_token to the SPA (via loginPopup/loginRedirect<br/>or acquireTokenSilent from cache).

    Browser->>IdP: GET /oauth2/v2.0/authorize (managed by msal-angular)
    Note over IdP: User authenticates.
    IdP-->>Browser: Auth code callback - msal-angular exchanges for id_token

    Browser->>Cognito: InitiateAuth<br/>AuthFlow=CUSTOM_AUTH, USERNAME=email<br/>clientMetadata={flow:"oidc_msal"}
    Note over Cognito: Invoke DefineAuthChallenge Lambda.
    Cognito->>DefineAuth: session=[] clientMetadata={flow:"oidc_msal"}
    Note over DefineAuth: Session is empty - first call.<br/>Reads flow from clientMetadata: oidc_msal.<br/>Sets challengeName=CUSTOM_CHALLENGE.
    DefineAuth-->>Cognito: challengeName=CUSTOM_CHALLENGE

    Note over Cognito: Invoke CreateAuthChallenge Lambda.
    Cognito->>CreateAuth: session=[] clientMetadata={flow:"oidc_msal"}
    Note over CreateAuth: Session is empty - reads flow from clientMetadata.<br/>flow=oidc_msal.<br/>Sets privateChallengeParameters.flow=oidc_msal<br/>and challengeMetadata=oidc_msal:OIDC_MSAL.
    CreateAuth-->>Cognito: publicParams={challenge_type:"oidc_msal"}<br/>privateParams={flow:"oidc_msal",auth_step:"OIDC_MSAL"}<br/>challengeMetadata="oidc_msal:OIDC_MSAL"

    Cognito-->>Browser: ChallengeName=CUSTOM_CHALLENGE, Session=S1<br/>ChallengeParameters={challenge_type:"oidc_msal",...}

    Browser->>Cognito: RespondToAuthChallenge<br/>ANSWER={"id_token":"<Entra JWT>","flow":"oidc_msal"}<br/>Session=S1
    Note over Cognito: Invoke VerifyAuthChallengeResponse Lambda.

    Cognito->>VerifyAuth: challengeAnswer={"id_token":"...","flow":"oidc_msal"}<br/>privateChallengeParameters={flow:"oidc_msal",auth_step:"OIDC_MSAL"}
    Note over VerifyAuth: Reads flow="oidc_msal" from privateChallengeParameters<br/>(authoritative - set by CreateAuthChallenge).<br/>Routes to OIDC_MSAL exchange handler.

    Note over VerifyAuth: Validate Entra id_token:<br/>1. Fetch JWKS from Entra discovery endpoint.<br/>2. Verify RSA-SHA256 signature.<br/>3. Validate iss, aud (EntraClientId), exp, tid.<br/>4. Extract email from trusted claims only.

    VerifyAuth->>Django: POST /api/internal/login-access-check/<br/>{"email":"user@...","login_method":"oidc","provider_name":"EntraOidc"}
    Django-->>VerifyAuth: 200 {"allowed":true,"django_id":"42"}

    VerifyAuth->>EnsureUser: action=ensure_oidc<br/>{email, django_user_id="42"}
    Note over EnsureUser: User not in Cognito. admin_create_user:<br/>custom:django_id="42", custom:auth_provider="oidc_msal".<br/>Random password set (never used for auth).
    EnsureUser-->>VerifyAuth: {"cognito_user_id":"sub-uuid"}

    VerifyAuth-->>Cognito: answerCorrect=true

    Cognito->>PreToken: userAttributes={email, custom:django_id="42",<br/>custom:auth_provider="oidc_msal"}
    Note over PreToken: custom:auth_provider=="oidc_msal" -> login_method="oidc"
    PreToken->>Django: POST /api/internal/login-access-check/<br/>{"email":"user@...","login_method":"oidc","provider_name":"EntraOidc"}
    Django-->>PreToken: 200 {"allowed":true,"django_id":"42"}
    PreToken-->>Cognito: claimsToAddOrOverride={django_id:"42"}

    Cognito-->>Browser: {id_token, access_token, refresh_token}
    Note over Browser: Cognito tokens stored. id_token contains django_id="42".
